{"parse":{"title":"Secular education","pageid":827398,"revid":854914584,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_(8).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg/220px-Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"148\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg/330px-Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg/440px-Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_%288%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2896\" data-file-height=\"1944\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Campus_San_Joaqu%C3%ADn_(8).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A crucifix in a classroom at the <a href=\"/wiki/Pontifical_Catholic_University_of_Chile\" title=\"Pontifical Catholic University of Chile\">Pontifical Catholic University of Chile</a>. Crucifixes in classrooms of public schools have become a matter of controversy in some countries.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Secular education</b> is a system of public education in countries with a <a href=\"/wiki/Secular\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Secular\">secular</a> government or <a href=\"/wiki/Separation_of_church_and_state\" title=\"Separation of church and state\">separation</a> between <a href=\"/wiki/Religion\" title=\"Religion\">religion</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Sovereign_state\" title=\"Sovereign state\">state</a>.\n</p><p>An example of a secular educational system would be the <a href=\"/wiki/Education_in_France\" title=\"Education in France\">French public educational system</a>, where <a href=\"/wiki/French_law_on_secularity_and_conspicuous_religious_symbols_in_schools\" title=\"French law on secularity and conspicuous religious symbols in schools\">conspicuous religious symbols</a> have been banned in schools. \nWhile some religious groups are hostile to secularism and see such measures as promoting <a href=\"/wiki/Atheism\" title=\"Atheism\">atheism</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> other citizens claim that the display of any religious symbol constitutes an infringement of the <a href=\"/wiki/Separation_of_church_and_state\" title=\"Separation of church and state\">separation of church and state</a> and a discrimination against atheist, agnostic and non-religious people.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Actions_and_controversies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Actions and controversies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Actions_and_controversies\">Actions and controversies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Secular_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Actions and controversies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>In <a href=\"/wiki/Turkey\" title=\"Turkey\">Turkey</a> the promotion of <a href=\"/wiki/%C4%B0mam_Hatip_school\" title=\"\u0130mam Hatip school\">Imam Hatip</a> Islamic schools by the government<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> following the March 2012 education reform bill, allegedly alarmed some Turkish citizens.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The Education Reform Bill was written without public debate or even discussion in the <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_National_Education_(Turkey)\" title=\"Ministry of National Education (Turkey)\">Ministry of National Education</a>'s own consultative body; it did not even figure in the government\u2019s 2011 election manifesto. Besides undermining <a href=\"/wiki/Turkish_secularism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Turkish secularism\">Turkish secularism</a>, the new measures would undermine educational standards and deepen social inequalities, according to education specialists. Turkey\u2019s leading universities, including <a href=\"/wiki/Sabanci_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sabanci University\">Sabanci University</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bosphorus_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bosphorus University\">Bosphorus University</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Middle_East_Technical_University\" title=\"Middle East Technical University\">Middle East Technical University</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Ko%C3%A7_University\" title=\"Ko\u00e7 University\">Ko\u00e7 University</a>, all issued press statements describing the reforms of 2012 as hastily conceived, retrograde and out of step with current thinking.<sup id=\"cite_ref-finkel_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-finkel-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In Italy the <a href=\"/wiki/Lautsi_v._Italy\" title=\"Lautsi v. Italy\">Lautsi v. Italy</a> case was brought before the <a href=\"/wiki/European_Court_of_Human_Rights\" title=\"European Court of Human Rights\">European Court of Human Rights</a> regarding the display of <a href=\"/wiki/Crucifix\" title=\"Crucifix\">crucifixes</a> in classrooms of state schools.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ECHR_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ECHR-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In <a href=\"/wiki/Romania\" title=\"Romania\">Romania</a> the <a href=\"/wiki/CNCD_Decision_323/2006\" title=\"CNCD Decision 323/2006\">CNCD Decision 323/2006</a> was brought to the CNCD by Emil Moise, a teacher and parent from <a href=\"/wiki/Buz%C4%83u_County\" title=\"Buz\u0103u County\">Buz\u0103u County</a>, regarding the public display of <a href=\"/wiki/Romanian_Orthodox_icons\" title=\"Romanian Orthodox icons\">Orthodox icons</a> in classrooms and was supported by some high-profile activists.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In 2009 a new body was formed, the <i>Australian Secular Lobby</i>, to promote secular education in Australia.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In <a href=\"/wiki/Southern_Thailand\" title=\"Southern Thailand\">Southern Thailand</a>, the secular educational system is being undermined by <a href=\"/wiki/South_Thailand_insurgency\" title=\"South Thailand insurgency\">insurgent groups</a> by means of the destruction of schools and the assassination of teachers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Secular_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/French_law_on_secularity_and_conspicuous_religious_symbols_in_schools\" title=\"French law on secularity and conspicuous religious symbols in schools\">French law on secularity and conspicuous religious symbols in schools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Humanum_Genus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Humanum Genus\">Humanum Genus</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Secular_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.missionislam.com/homed/response.htm\">The Islamic Response to the Secular Educational System</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.asianews.it/news-en/Turkish-government-promoting-Islamic-schools-at-the-expense-of-secular-education-28824.html\">Asia News 08/24/2013 Turkish government promoting Islamic schools at the expense of secular education</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thenational.ae/world/europe/rise-of-islamic-schools-causes-alarm-in-secular-turkey\">The National - Rise of Islamic schools causes alarm in secular Turkey</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-finkel-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-finkel_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Andrew Finkel in the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Herald_Tribune\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"International Herald Tribune\">International Herald Tribune</a> of 23 March 2012 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/03/23/turkeys-education-reform-bill-is-about-playing-politics-with-pedagogy/\">What\u2019s 4 + 4 + 4?</a>; accessed on 7 November 2012</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ECHR-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ECHR_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.echr.coe.int/echr/resources/hudoc/lautsi_and_others_v__italy.pdf\">Full text of the judgment of the European Court of Human Rights</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cmiskp.echr.coe.int/tkp197/view.asp?action=open&amp;documentId=883171&amp;portal=hbkm&amp;source=externalbydocnumber&amp;table=F69A27FD8FB86142BF01C1166DEA398649\">Press release of the European Court of Human Rights</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://religionclause.blogspot.com/2011/03/european-courts-grand-chamber-upholds.html\">Summary of the ruling by the European Court of Human Rights</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Adriana Petrescu et al., <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://romania.indymedia.org/ro/2006/11/1713.shtml\">Scrisoare catre CNCD re: simboluri religioase</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20070102035609/http://www.romania.indymedia.org/ro/2006/11/1713.shtml\">Archived</a> 2007-01-02 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>. (\"Letter to the CNCD re: religious symbols\"), Indymedia Rom\u00e2na, 13 November 2006.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.abc.net.au/religion/articles/2012/10/22/3615647.htm\"><i>Faith in schools: The dismantling of Australia's secular public education system</i> by Chrys Stevenson</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/reports/thailand0807.pdf\"><i>No one is safe - The Ongoing Insurgency in Southern Thailand: Trends in Violence, Counterinsurgency Operations, and the Impact of National Politics</i></a>, by Zachary Abuza, <a href=\"/wiki/Human_Rights_Watch\" title=\"Human Rights Watch\">Human Rights Watch</a>, p. 23</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Secular_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.michaelnugent.com/2010/03/11/the-case-for-a-secular-education-system/\">The case for a secular education system</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.education.vic.gov.au/about/department/legislation/pages/act2006secular.aspx\">Principle of Secular Education</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.c.s